<h1>
    Cats
</h1>
<h2>
    What are cats?
</h2>
<p>
Cats (Felis catus) are small domesticated carnivorous mammals that belong to the family Felidae. They are known for their agility, playful behavior, 
and ability to hunt vermin. Domestication of cats is believed to have occurred around 7500 BC in the Near East, and they are commonly kept as pets and companions today
</p>
<h2>
    Kinds of cat colours
</h2>
<h3>
    Orange
</h3>
<p>
    Orange cats, often referred to as ginger or marmalade cats, are known for their vibrant personalities, affectionate nature, and distinctive coat patterns
</p>
<a href="orange-cats.html">More...</a>
